    "body": "### Language server\n\n_No response_\n\n### Requested feature\n\nI sometimes have to load files from a huge cpp project. nvim-lspconfig and clangd help me navigate those files easily. But after closing all the buffers, clangd process is not killed, and continues to use a lot of memory.\r\n\r\nMaybe lsp-config could detach the buffer from the client on BufUnload, and stop the client if it does not any active buffer left.\n\n### Other clients which have this feature\n\n_No response_",
